# Claude Instructions for OSS Contribution Work

## Samaritan Protocol (MANDATORY)

1. Read CONTRIBUTING.md and any AI policy before every submission
2. Understand the codebase section before touching it
3. One repo at a time, go deep
4. Co-Authored-By on every commit
5. Stay for the review (iterate on feedback within 24 hours)
6. After merge, stay engaged with the project
7. Never spray PRs
8. If in doubt about value, don't submit

## Critical Rules

- **NEVER push without explicit approval.**
- **NEVER commit unless explicitly asked.**
- **Co-Authored-By on every commit:**
  ```
  Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
  ```

## Review Cadence

- Every 3 days: check all active PRs for new comments/reviews
- Review feedback received: address within 24 hours
- No review after 7 days: polite ping
- No review after 14 days: assess if repo is active, consider closing

## Anti-AI Policy Watch List

Check before submitting to any new repo:
- NetBSD, QEMU, Gentoo, GNOME: outright ban
- Ghostty: zero tolerance, permanent ban risk
- MicroPython: mandatory AI disclosure
- tldraw: auto-closes external PRs

## Code Review Standards

Every review must have:
- Specific findings (bugs, edge cases, security, missing tests)
- Constructive tone
- Code examples where applicable
- No "LGTM" reviews. If you can't find anything substantive, don't review.

## PR Standards

Before submitting any PR:
- [ ] Read CONTRIBUTING.md
- [ ] Check for AI policy
- [ ] Understand the codebase context (not just the file)
- [ ] Check for competing PRs on the same issue
- [ ] Run tests locally if possible
- [ ] Create changeset if the repo uses them
- [ ] Co-Authored-By tag on all commits
